-- Mangalore Refinery Offers Vacuum Gasoil for February Loading
-- B y   A n n   K o h
-- 2011-12-27T02:30:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-27/mangalore-refinery-offers-vacuum-gasoil-for-february-loading.html
Mangalore Refinery & Petrochemicals
Ltd. (MRPL) , a unit of India’s largest energy explorer, offered to sell
vacuum gasoil for February loading, according to a document sent
to potential buyers on Dec. 23.  Details of the offer follow below:  Vacuum gasoil is a refinery distillate that can be used to
make fuels like gasoline and diesel.  Oil & Natural Gas Corp. (ONGC) ,
the country’s largest oil explorer, owns about 72 percent of
Mangalore Refinery.  To contact the reporter on this story:
